-- в”Ђв”Ђ Tabnine в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Tabnine is an AI code assistant that provides in-IDE code completion, chat, and autonomous coding agents, built around enterprise privacy controls like zero data retention and on-premises deployment.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$39/user/month (Code Assistant plan, billed annually)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Tel Aviv, Israel$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Tabnine Review 2026: AI Code Assistant Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Tabnine is a privacy-focused AI code assistant for enterprise teams. See 2026 pricing plans, key features, pros and cons, and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Tabnine is an AI code assistant originally founded in 2013 in Tel Aviv, Israel, under the name Codota by Dror Weiss and Eran Yahav, and rebranded to Tabnine in 2021. It provides AI-powered code completion, in-IDE chat, and autonomous coding agents across major integrated development environments, with a strong emphasis on enterprise privacy, including zero code retention, IP-indemnified suggestions trained on permissively licensed code, and flexible deployment options such as SaaS, virtual private cloud, on-premises, and fully air-gapped environments. Tabnine retired its free individual tier in 2025 and, as of 2026, sells two primary annually billed subscription plans: Code Assistant at 39 dollars per user per month for completions and chat, and Agentic Platform at 59 dollars per user per month, which adds autonomous AI agents, Model Context Protocol tool integrations, and a command-line interface for terminal-based workflows, plus a custom-priced Enterprise tier for air-gapped and highly regulated deployments. The company is headquartered in Tel Aviv, Israel, with roughly 50 to 200 employees, and is positioned toward engineering organizations in regulated industries such as finance, healthcare, and government that need AI coding assistance without sending proprietary code to third-party servers.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'd2aef943-d551-456d-b2f7-bd530c268780';

